title: Tiggras Been There
name: Tiggras Been There
description:
A Map by Tiggra

Places I've lived or visited.

properties.name: 7711 Ponoma Trail, Austin Texas
properties.description: Posted by TiggraI pretty much grew up in this house.. off and on since I was a freshman in highschool.

properties.name: Antigua, Guatemala
properties.description: Posted by TiggraA beautiful colonial town with lots to see, very active night life, dozens of spanish language schools, and a good center point for travel around Guatemala.

properties.name: Asheville, NC
properties.description: Posted by TiggraOne of my favorite houses I lived in growing up. Fields in front and behind the house, a huge garden, abandon barns and houses, woods to get lost in. From the satellite picture it doesn\'t look like the house is still standing.

properties.name: Austin, Texas
properties.description: Posted by TiggraHome (currently)

properties.name: Bay of Pigs, Cuba
properties.description: Posted by TiggraExcellent diving! 300 ft. + Vis., good sea life, and a few wrecks.

properties.name: Belize City, Belize
properties.description: Posted by TiggraCheapest Airport in Central Amer., busy city with a few sites and things to do but mostly a center point to travel from.

properties.name: Charleston, SC
properties.description: Posted by TiggraBorn on the Naval Base in Charleston, SC

properties.name: Corinto, Honduras
properties.description: Posted by TiggraCorinto, Hond. a small village on the Guatemala / Honduras border. I crossed over the border at night on foot.. the border consist of a wooden sign that simply says Honduras. Corinto is the only thing around and has a 4 room hotel and 1 resturant. People are really nice here.

properties.name: El Mirador, Guatemala
properties.description: Posted by TiggraEl Mirador is a lost mayan city deep in the jungle with 1200+ ft temples and dozens of smaller buildings. I hiked 70 km thru the jungle to spend a few nights here. Really somewhere that has to be experienced to understand the beauty and mystery.

properties.name: Graceland
properties.description: Posted by TiggraMade this stop with my sister once, I am not sure which is more outrageous... Graceland in all its glory or the people that take the tour...

properties.name: Graceland
properties.description: Posted by JamesGracelandToured Elvis\' house

properties.name: Granada, Nicaragua
properties.description: Posted by TiggraGranada is a colonial town on the shore of Lake Nicaragua. Beautiful buildings, history, and the views of the lake and volcanoes. There are a lot of tourist but still a great city to spend a few days in.

properties.name: Havana, Cuba
properties.description: Posted by TiggraA living museum full of secrets. Spent a couple weeks here exploring the city, walking up and down the streets in Old Havana, sitting and talking to nationals on the sea wall. Truly worth the visit.

properties.name: Las Vegas, Nevada
properties.description: Posted by Tiggra

properties.name: New Orleans, LA
properties.description: Posted by TiggraLived in a broken down car in this parking lot for 3 months.

properties.name: Organ Pipe Cactus National Park
properties.description: Posted by TiggraÂ Great park, huge 20ft pipe cactus, and a good jump off for Mexico. Camp ground sucks with sites 10 ft from each other in all directions.

properties.name: Panama City, Panama
properties.description: Posted by TiggraI spent about a week here, lots of cheap shopping, a few sites to see, and very moderized compared to the majority of Central America.

properties.name: Poneloya, Nicaragua
properties.description: Posted by TiggraPoneloya is just a small beach town an hour west of Leon with big surf, quiet nights, and a maze of turneffes. I spent a week or so here chillin.

properties.name: Roswell, NM
properties.description: Posted by TiggraRoswell, NM.. kind of a tourist trap but a good stop on a road trip. Even the front of Walmart has a alien on it.

properties.name: San Diego, CA
properties.description: Posted by TiggraSan Diego is always a blast. Easy to get around and tons to do. The point is on the hostel I stay at before heading down the Baja.. nice clean place in the middle of downtown.

properties.name: San Francisco, Ca
properties.description: Posted by TiggraSan Fran is blast.. exspensive but fun. Tons of things to see and do.

properties.name: Seattle, Wa
properties.description: Posted by Tiggra

properties.name: St. Louis
properties.description: Posted by TiggraSt. Louis has tons to do with lots of history.

properties.name: Utila, Bay Islands, Honduras
properties.description: Posted by TiggraUtila, Honduras is an small island just east of La Cieba, Hond. I spent a few months here working at Underwater Vision Dive Shop. Excellent diving, Whaleshark sightings, wild night life, freshwater caves, and a great mix of locals and travellers.

properties.name: White Sands NP, New Mexico
properties.description: Posted by TiggraBeautiful White sand dunes excellent for a solo escape from the world.
